{"id":14880766,"mediaExerciseId":"1c47329c-e14e-4785-ba26-c72f5ced003a","exerciseName":"15","chapterName":"2","chapterTitle":"Financial Statements, Taxes, and Cash Flow","groupId":612265,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":44,"solutions":[{"id":5904447,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"This exercise requires us to compute the market value of the shareholders equity.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"**Market value** is the cost price currently offered for an asset or services in the market.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":66,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/19/5c01c576a3ef8bb4cc1ec4a0b3792696/571809adb53ad9937369bfb31c5b448a/lateximg_large.png","width":995},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/19/5c01c576a3ef8bb4cc1ec4a0b3792696/571809adb53ad9937369bfb31c5b448a/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"The Market Value of the Shareholders' Equity is computed as follows:\n\n$$ \\begin{aligned}\n\\text{MV of Shareholders' Equity} &= \\text{MV of  Assets} - {\\text{MV of Liabilities}}\\\\[1pt]\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nWhere:\n\nMV - Market Value","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":63,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/19/5c01c576a3ef8bb4cc1ec4a0b3792696/b0d7de73254a2356007042d446d41c06/lateximg_large.png","width":994},"regular":{"height":32,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/19/5c01c576a3ef8bb4cc1ec4a0b3792696/b0d7de73254a2356007042d446d41c06/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"## Requirement A\n\nIn this first scenario, the market value of the assets is $9,400. Now, we can compute the market value of shareholders' equity using the formula in step 3.\n\n$$ \\begin{aligned}\n\\text{MV of Shareholders' Equity} &= \\text{MV of  Assets} - {\\text{MV of Liabilities}}\\\\[5pt]\n&= \\text{\\$9,400} - {\\text{7,800}}\\\\[5pt]\n&=\\underline{\\underline{ \\textbf{\\$1,600}}}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nTherefore, the market value of Bishop, Inc. shareholders' equity is **$1,600**.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":192,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/19/5c01c576a3ef8bb4cc1ec4a0b3792696/fda982ea269562c1ff23ed0f4f8ce9ca/lateximg_large.png","width":928},"regular":{"height":98,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/19/5c01c576a3ef8bb4cc1ec4a0b3792696/fda982ea269562c1ff23ed0f4f8ce9ca/lateximg.png","width":463}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"## Requirement A\n\nIn this next scenario, the market value of the assets is $6,700. Since the market value of liabilities amounting to $7,800, it is greater than the assets, and the result will be negative. \n\nThe market value of shareholders' equity cannot be negative. Hence, the answer will be **$0**.\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"3d924bbc-775b-4106-8bde-c15fdd638ac9","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":5}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14880767,"exerciseName":"16","page":44,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"a7888871-fed6-48ea-bb7c-2682dc2b1f73","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-2-questions-and-problems-16-a7888871-fed6-48ea-bb7c-2682dc2b1f73"},{"id":14880768,"exerciseName":"17","page":45,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"0f1d6809-5672-4377-90cc-71bcfba03ed2","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-2-questions-and-problems-17-0f1d6809-5672-4377-90cc-71bcfba03ed2"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14880765,"exerciseName":"14","page":44,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"f3f333dc-0909-45ff-b451-73d2e1bcf30c","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-2-questions-and-problems-14-f3f333dc-0909-45ff-b451-73d2e1bcf30c"},{"id":14880764,"exerciseName":"13","page":44,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"b4b6f99b-1f95-41ac-9da6-d3d2c5f09c33","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-2-questions-and-problems-13-b4b6f99b-1f95-41ac-9da6-d3d2c5f09c33"}],"_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-2-questions-and-problems-15-1c47329c-e14e-4785-ba26-c72f5ced003a"}